comments.text: Please be advised that infrared thermal imaging may be utilized to assess specific areas or systems for potential anomalies. Any indications observed through thermal imaging are always corroborated by supplementary methods, such as a moisture meter, to confirm their presence. The effectiveness of infrared thermography in detecting moisture is contingent upon the actual presence of moisture; therefore, during dry periods, a leak may exist but remain undetectable if the affected materials are devoid of moisture. It is crucial to understand that thermal imaging does not function as X-ray vision, cannot penetrate solid surfaces, and is not capable of identifying mold.
